# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. NEVER commit real secrets; NEVER paste them into a chat.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOCAL DEV + MOCK BENCH  →  runs on your CLAUDE SUBSCRIPTION, no key needed here.
#   Authenticate the Claude Code CLI ONCE:  `claude setup-token`  (or `claude login`).
#   The Agent SDK (harness) picks it up automatically. This is the free-ish loop — use it heavily.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEPLOY TO THE CMA WORKSPACE  (deploy/port.py)  →  your PARTICIPANT Anthropic key from 1Password.
#   Workspace: hack-2026-t32  ·  SPEND CAP: $50 (shared across the team — spend it only on real
#   bench validation, not iteration). Use YOUR key, NEVER the judge key.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# COMPANY MCP  (the McContext data/tools)  →  URL + token you're handed. Referenced from agent.yaml
#   as ${MCCTX_MCP_URL} etc. Keep the token here, out of any committed agent.yaml.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MCCTX_MCP_URL=
# MCCTX_MCP_TOKEN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OBSERVABILITY  (optional)  →  Claude Code + the Agent SDK emit OpenTelemetry from these vars, so
#   tracing your local harness AND your own Claude Code sessions is the same config. Start the sink
#   with `make trace-up` (HyperDX, one container), then `source` these. Details: traces/README.md.
#   http/protobuf on 4318 is the universal default (Claude Code's own examples use gRPC/4317, which
#   silently fails against Langfuse). Keep content-logging OFF unless debugging a specific failure.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_TELEMETRY=1
# CLAUDE_CODE_ENHANCED_TELEMETRY_BETA=1          # traces are beta — needed for the span tree
# OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER=otlp
# OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER=otlp
# OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER=otlp
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL=http/protobuf
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4318
# OTEL_METRIC_EXPORT_INTERVAL=1000               # short agent runs: flush fast or spans drop on exit
# OTEL_LOGS_EXPORT_INTERVAL=1000
# OTEL_TRACES_EXPORT_INTERVAL=1000
# OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=t32-harness                  # set per agent to separate them on the sink
